Bowenia serrulata.label: Bowenia serrulata
Bowenia serrulata.description: The Byfield Fern is a species of plant in the Stangeriaceae family. It is consequently not a fern as its vernacular name or appearance may suggest. It is endemic to the vicinity of Byfield, Australia. Wikipedia

Ceratozamia.label: Ceratozamia
Ceratozamia.description: Ceratozamia is a genus of New World cycads in the family Zamiaceae. The genus contains 26 currently living species and one or two fossil species. Wikipedia

Bowenia spectabilis.label: Bowenia spectabilis
Bowenia spectabilis.description: Bowenia spectabilis is a species of plant in the Stangeriaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests. Wikipedia

Cycas beddomei.label: Cycas beddomei
Cycas beddomei.description: Cycas beddomei is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to India, where it is confined to a small area of Andhra Pradesh state in the Tirumala Hills in scrubland and brush covered hills. Wikipedia

Cycas circinalis.label: Cycas circinalis
Cycas circinalis.description: Cycas circinalis, also known as the queen sago, is a type of cycad. Wikipedia

Macrozamia.label: Macrozamia
Macrozamia.description: Macrozamia is a genus of 38-40 species of cycads, in the family Zamiaceae, endemic to Australia. The majority of the species occur in eastern Australia in southeast Queensland and New South Wales, with ... Wikipedia

Microcycas.label: Microcycas
Microcycas.description: Microcycas is a genus of cycads in the family Zamiaceae containing only one species, Microcycas calocoma, endemic to a small area in western Cuba in Pinar del Río Province. Wikipedia

Zamia angustifolia.label: Zamia angustifolia
Zamia angustifolia.description: Zamia angustifolia is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in the Bahamas and Cuba. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Stangeria.label: Stangeria
Stangeria.description: Stangeria eriopus is a cycad endemic to southern Africa It is the sole species in the genus Stangeria, most closely related to the Australian genus Bowenia, with which it forms the family Stangeriaceae. Wikipedia

Zamia integrifolia.label: Zamia integrifolia
Zamia integrifolia.description:
Zamia integrifolia is a small, tough, woody cycad native to the southeast United States, the Bahamas and the Caribbean south to Grand Cayman and Puerto Rico.
This cycad produces reddish seed cones with a distinct acuminate tip. Wikipedia

Zamiaceae.label: Zamiaceae
Zamiaceae.description: The Zamiaceae are a family of cycads that are superficially palm or fern-like. They are divided into two subfamilies with eight genera and about 150 species in the tropical and warm temperate regions of Africa, Australia and North and South America. Wikipedia

Cycas revoluta.label: Cycas revoluta
Cycas revoluta.description: Cycas revoluta, is a species of gymnosperm in the family Cycadaceae, native to southern Japan. It is one of several species used for the production of sago, as well as an ornamental plant. Wikipedia

Cycas pruinosa.label: Cycas pruinosa
Cycas pruinosa.description: Cycas pruinosa is a small to medium species of cycad, a seed plant. It is a widespread but sporadic species in the eastern and southern Kimberley region of Western Australia, occurring also in the Spirit ... Wikipedia

Ceratozamia becerrae.label: Ceratozamia becerrae
Ceratozamia becerrae.description: Ceratozamia becerrae is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Ceratozamia mixeorum.label: Ceratozamia mixeorum
Ceratozamia mixeorum.description: Ceratozamia mixeorum is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. Wikipedia

Ceratozamia morettii.label: Ceratozamia morettii
Ceratozamia morettii.description: Ceratozamia morettii is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia fischeri.label: Zamia fischeri
Zamia fischeri.description: Zamia fischeri is a species of cycad in the Zamiaceae family. It is often confused with Zamia vazquezii. Zamia fischeri is named after Gustav Fischer, a cycad enthusiast of the nineteenth century. Wikipedia

Encephalartos villosus.label: Encephalartos villosus
Encephalartos villosus.description: Encephalartos villosus is a South African cycad occurring from the East London vicinity, where it is found near the coast, to the northern border of Swaziland where it may grow as far as 100 km inland. Wikipedia

Encephalartos woodii.label: Encephalartos woodii
Encephalartos woodii.description: Wood's Cycad is a cycad in the genus Encephalartos, and is endemic to the Ongoye Forest of KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. It is one of the rarest plants in the world, being extinct in the wild with all specimens being clones of the type. Wikipedia

Lepidozamia.label: Lepidozamia
Lepidozamia.description: Lepidozamia is a genus of two species of cycad, native to Australia. The name, derived from the Greek word lepidos, meaning scaly, refers to the scale-like structure of the stem and leaf bases. Wikipedia

Cycas aculeata.label: Cycas aculeata
Cycas aculeata.description:
Cycas aculeata is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to Vietnam, where it is endemic to a single site on the south slopes of the Hai Van Pass.
It has a short subterranean stem 15-18 cm diameter, which bears 6-23 leaves. Wikipedia

Cycas angulata.label: Cycas angulata
Cycas angulata.description: Cycas angulata is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to Australia in northeast Northern Territory and northwest Queensland. Wikipedia

Cycas apoa.label: Cycas apoa
Cycas apoa.description:
Cycas apoa is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to northern New Guinea. It occurs in the Sepik River basin, in wet lowland forest in modestly seasonally flooded areas.
It has erect stems up to 2.5 m tall. Wikipedia

Cycas arenicola.label: Cycas arenicola
Cycas arenicola.description: Cycas arenicola is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to Australia, in the far north of Northern Territory in the basin of the upper East Alligator River in Arnhem Land. It grows in Eucalyptus woodlands on highly siliceous soils. Wikipedia

Cycas arnhemica.label: Cycas arnhemica
Cycas arnhemica.description:
Cycas arnhemica is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to Australia, in the northwest of Northern Territory in Arnhem Land, after which it is named.
The stems are erect, growing to 1.5-2.5 m tall. Wikipedia

Cycas badensis.label: Cycas badensis
Cycas badensis.description:
Cycas badensis is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to Australia, in the extreme north of Queensland, where it is endemic on Badu Island in the Torres Strait Islands.
The stems grow up to 8 m tall. Wikipedia

Cycas balansae.label: Cycas balansae
Cycas balansae.description: Cycas balansae is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to southwestern China and adjacent northern Vietnam, where it occurs in dense mountain rainforests. Wikipedia

Cycas basaltica.label: Cycas basaltica
Cycas basaltica.description: Cycas basaltica is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to Australia, in the far north of Western Australia in the Kimberley region. Wikipedia

Cycas cairnsiana.label: Cycas cairnsiana
Cycas cairnsiana.description:
Cycas cairnsiana is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to northern Australia in northern Queensland on the Newcastle Range.
The stems grow to 2-5 m tall and 12-16 cm diameter, with swollen base. Wikipedia

Cycas calcicola.label: Cycas calcicola
Cycas calcicola.description:
Cycas calcicola is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to northern Australia in the northwest of Northern Territory.
The stems are erect, 2-5 m tall and 16-22 cm diameter. Wikipedia

Cycas campestris.label: Cycas campestris
Cycas campestris.description: Cycas campestris is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to southeastern Papua New Guinea in the lowland region near Port Moresby. It grows in open, grassy locations, often in areas with frequent grass fires. Wikipedia

Cycas chamaoensis.label: Cycas chamaoensis
Cycas chamaoensis.description: Cycas chamaoensis is named after the only known habitat of this species, on and near Khao Chamao mountain in Khao Chamao District, Thailand. Stems are arborescent, either erect or decumbent. Wikipedia

Dioon spinulosum.label: Dioon spinulosum
Dioon spinulosum.description: Dioon spinulosum, giant dioon, or gum palm, is a cycad endemic to limestone cliffs and rocky hillsides in the tropical rainforests of Veracruz and Oaxaca, Mexico. It is one of the tallest cycads in the world, growing to 12m in height. Wikipedia

Encephalartos ferox.label: Encephalartos ferox
Encephalartos ferox.description: Encephalartos ferox, a member of the family Zamiaceae, is a small cycad with 35 cm wide subterranean trunk. It gets its name from the Latin word ferocious, likely from the spine-tipped lobes on the leaves of the plant. Wikipedia

Encephalartos horridus.label: Encephalartos horridus
Encephalartos horridus.description: The Eastern Cape Blue Cycad is a small, low-growing cycad up to 0.9m high and 0.9m wide. It is a native of Eastern Cape Province, South Africa, and found in arid shrublands, most commonly on ridges and slopes with shallow soils. Wikipedia

Encephalartos lehmannii.label: Encephalartos lehmannii
Encephalartos lehmannii.description: Encephalartos lehmannii is a low-growing palm-like cycad in the family Zamiaceae. It is commonly known as the Karoo cycad and is endemic to South Africa. The species name lehmannii commemorates Prof J.G.C. Wikipedia

Encephalartos transvenosus.label: Encephalartos transvenosus
Encephalartos transvenosus.description: Encephalartos transvenosus is a palm-like cycad in the family Zamiaceae. It is found in Limpopo Province in South Africa. It is also sometimes called "Modjadji's palm" and is named after the Rain Queen. Wikipedia

Lepidozamia hopei.label: Lepidozamia hopei
Lepidozamia hopei.description: Lepidozamia hopei is a species of cycad in the Zamiaceae family. Its English common name is "Hope's Cycad." It is endemic to the Australian state of Queensland. It is the largest known species of cycad. Wikipedia

Macrozamia macdonnellii.label: Macrozamia macdonnellii
Macrozamia macdonnellii.description:
Macrozamia macdonnellii is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia.
Macrozamia macdonnellii is not eaten by the Arrernte people of the Macdonnell Ranges due to the extensive process of toxin leaching that is required. Wikipedia

Neuropteris.label: Neuropteris
Neuropteris.description: Neuropteris is an extinct seed fern that existed in the Carboniferous period, known only from fossils. Major species include Neuropteris loschi. Wikipedia

Ceratozamia euryphyllidia.label: Ceratozamia euryphyllidia
Ceratozamia euryphyllidia.description: Ceratozamia euryphyllidia is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Guatemala and Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Ceratozamia whitelockiana.label: Ceratozamia whitelockiana
Ceratozamia whitelockiana.description: Ceratozamia whitelockiana is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Cycas armstrongii.label: Cycas armstrongii
Cycas armstrongii.description:
Cycas armstrongii is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to Australia, in the northwest of Northern Territory from the Finniss River in the west to the Arnhem Highway to the east.
The stems reach 3 m tall, with a diameter of 5–11 cm. Wikipedia

Cycas bifida.label: Cycas bifida
Cycas bifida.description:
Cycas bifida is a species of cycad plant in the genus Cycas, native to southern China, and northern Vietnam.
The stems are largely subterranean, 20–60 cm in diameter and up to 20 cm above ground level, and bear three to eight leaves. Wikipedia

Cycas brachycantha.label: Cycas brachycantha
Cycas brachycantha.description: Cycas brachycantha is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to northern Vietnam where it is endemic to Bắc Kạn Province. It grows in often soil-free cracks and crevices of limestone crests and ridges under the canopy of evergreen forests. Wikipedia

Cycas brunnea.label: Cycas brunnea
Cycas brunnea.description: Cycas brunnea is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to northern Australia in northwest Queensland and northeast Northern Territory in a small area straddling the border of the two regions. Wikipedia

Cycas canalis.label: Cycas canalis
Cycas canalis.description: Cycas canalis is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas, native to northern Australia in the northwest of Northern Territory, where it occurs in two areas, on the coast at Channel Point, and inland in the Daly River area near Dorisvale. Wikipedia

Cycas micronesica.label: Cycas micronesica
Cycas micronesica.description: Cycas micronesica is a type of cycad found in Micronesia, the Marianas Group and the western Caroline Islands. The species, previously lumped with Cycas rumphii or Cycas circinalis, was described in 1994 by Ken Hill. Wikipedia

Macrozamia crassifolia.label: Macrozamia crassifolia
Macrozamia crassifolia.description: Macrozamia crassifolia is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia diplomera.label: Macrozamia diplomera
Macrozamia diplomera.description: Macrozamia diplomera is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia douglasii.label: Macrozamia douglasii
Macrozamia douglasii.description: Macrozamia douglasii is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Queensland, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia fawcettii.label: Macrozamia fawcettii
Macrozamia fawcettii.description: Macrozamia fawcettii is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia heteromera.label: Macrozamia heteromera
Macrozamia heteromera.description: Macrozamia heteromera is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia fearnsidei.label: Macrozamia fearnsidei
Macrozamia fearnsidei.description: Macrozamia fearnsidei is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia humilis.label: Macrozamia humilis
Macrozamia humilis.description: Macrozamia humilis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Inverell in New South Wales, Australia. Its natural habitat is on granite soils in temperate shrubby woodland forests. Wikipedia

Macrozamia longispina.label: Macrozamia longispina
Macrozamia longispina.description: Macrozamia longispina is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia montana.label: Macrozamia montana
Macrozamia montana.description: Macrozamia montana is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia mountperriensis.label: Macrozamia mountperriensis
Macrozamia mountperriensis.description: Macrozamia mountperriensis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Queensland, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia occidua.label: Macrozamia occidua
Macrozamia occidua.description: Macrozamia occidua is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical dry forests. Wikipedia

Macrozamia parcifolia.label: Macrozamia parcifolia
Macrozamia parcifolia.description: Macrozamia parcifolia is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia pauli-guilielmi.label: Macrozamia pauli-guilielmi
Macrozamia pauli-guilielmi.description: Macrozamia pauli-guilielmi is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia polymorpha.label: Macrozamia polymorpha
Macrozamia polymorpha.description: Macrozamia polymorpha is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia reducta.label: Macrozamia reducta
Macrozamia reducta.description: Macrozamia reducta is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia secunda.label: Macrozamia secunda
Macrozamia secunda.description: Macrozamia secunda is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia, where rainfall is fairly constant throughout the year. Wikipedia

Macrozamia stenomera.label: Macrozamia stenomera
Macrozamia stenomera.description: Macrozamia stenomera is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia viridis.label: Macrozamia viridis
Macrozamia viridis.description: Macrozamia viridis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Cycas media.label: Cycas media
Cycas media.description: Cycas media is a palm-like tall shrub native to woodlands of Queensland, Australia. The leathery, thick leaves are divided and grow from the center in a palm-like arrangement. All plant parts are considered highly toxic. Wikipedia

Cycas taiwaniana.label: Cycas taiwaniana
Cycas taiwaniana.description: Cycas taiwaniana is a species of genus Cycas. The species is native to Guangdong, Guangxi and Fujian in China. Wikipedia

Macrozamia cardiacensis.label: Macrozamia cardiacensis
Macrozamia cardiacensis.description: Macrozamia cardiacensis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia conferta.label: Macrozamia conferta
Macrozamia conferta.description: Macrozamia conferta is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia flexuosa.label: Macrozamia flexuosa
Macrozamia flexuosa.description: Macrozamia flexuosa is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia cranei.label: Macrozamia cranei
Macrozamia cranei.description: Macrozamia cranei is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical dry forests. Wikipedia

Macrozamia lucida.label: Macrozamia lucida
Macrozamia lucida.description: Macrozamia lucida is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia miquelii.label: Macrozamia miquelii

Macrozamia platyrhachis.description: Macrozamia platyrhachis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia spiralis.label: Macrozamia spiralis
Macrozamia spiralis.description: Macrozamia spiralis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to New South Wales in eastern Australia. Wikipedia

Zamia encephalartoides.label: Zamia encephalartoides
Zamia encephalartoides.description: Zamia encephalartoides is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Colombia. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia poeppigiana.label: Zamia poeppigiana
Zamia poeppigiana.description: Zamia poeppigiana is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Colombia, Ecuador, and Peru. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia urep.label: Zamia urep
Zamia urep.description: Zamia urep is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Peru. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Bowenia.label: Bowenia
Bowenia.description: The genus Bowenia, includes two living and two fossil species of cycads in the family Zamiaceae, sometimes placed on their own family Boweniaceae. They are entirely restricted to Australia. Wikipedia

Zamia.label: Zamia
Zamia.description: Zamia is a genus of cycad of the family Zamiaceae, containing around 50 species, native to North, Central and South America. Species occur as far north as Georgia in the United States to as far south as Bolivia. Wikipedia

Macrozamia communis.label: Macrozamia communis
Macrozamia communis.description: Macrozamia communis is an Australian cycad found on the east coast of New South Wales. The common name for the species is burrawang, a word derived from the Daruk Australian Aboriginal language; this ... Wikipedia

Macrozamia riedlei.label: Macrozamia riedlei
Macrozamia riedlei.description: Macrozamia riedlei is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Western Australia. Found on lateritic soils and in Jarrah forests. Wikipedia

Ceratozamia fuscoviridis.label: Ceratozamia fuscoviridis
Ceratozamia fuscoviridis.description: Ceratozamia fuscoviridis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia acuminata.label: Zamia acuminata
Zamia acuminata.description: Zamia acuminata is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family which is threatened by habitat loss. It is found in Costa Rica, Nicaragua, and Panama. Wikipedia

Zamia amblyphyllidia.label: Zamia amblyphyllidia
Zamia amblyphyllidia.description: Zamia amblyphyllidia is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Cuba, Jamaica, and Puerto Rico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia dressleri.label: Zamia dressleri
Zamia dressleri.description: Zamia dressleri is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Panama. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia hymenophyllidia.label: Zamia hymenophyllidia
Zamia hymenophyllidia.description: Zamia hymenophyllidia is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Colombia and Peru. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia ipetiensis.label: Zamia ipetiensis
Zamia ipetiensis.description: Zamia ipetiensis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Panama. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia kickxii.label: Zamia kickxii
Zamia kickxii.description: Zamia kickxii is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Cuba. Wikipedia

Zamia lacandona.label: Zamia lacandona
Zamia lacandona.description: Zamia lacandona is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia obliqua.label: Zamia obliqua
Zamia obliqua.description: Zamia obliqua is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Colombia and Panama. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia monticola.label: Zamia monticola
Zamia monticola.description: Zamia monticola is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Guatemala. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia polymorpha.label: Zamia polymorpha
Zamia polymorpha.description: Zamia polymorpha is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Belize and Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia portoricensis.label: Zamia portoricensis
Zamia portoricensis.description: Zamia portoricensis is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Puerto Rico. Wikipedia

Zamia pseudoparasitica.label: Zamia pseudoparasitica
Zamia pseudoparasitica.description: Zamia pseudoparasitica is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Panama. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia pseudomonticola.label: Zamia pseudomonticola
Zamia pseudomonticola.description: Zamia pseudomonticola is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Costa Rica and Panama. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia variegata.label: Zamia variegata
Zamia variegata.description: Zamia variegata is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is found in Guatemala and Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia prasina.label: Zamia prasina
Zamia prasina.description: Zamia prasina is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Belize. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Zamia vazquezii.label: Zamia vazquezii
Zamia vazquezii.description: Zamia vazquezii is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia
